cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with reinforcement learning and value function decomposition. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing methods for learning with temporal and state abstractions. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as hierarchical RL is often used in robotics applications. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as RL is a popular method for control systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as RL is often used in multi-agent settings.
